    <div class="intro-text" style="background:#f1f5f9; border-left-color:#64748b;">
        ✅ <strong>Conclusion:</strong> Creating tables is a fundamental operation in MySQL. 
        The <code>CREATE TABLE</code> statement allows you to define the structure of your data with columns, data types, and constraints. 
        You can create tables from the command line, copy existing tables, or use client programs. 
        Always choose appropriate data types and constraints to ensure data integrity and performance.
    </div>

    <footer>
